claim: In 1932, Pep Comics introduced the first superhero to die.
premise_source_doc_sentence: Pep Comics was the comics title that introduced the superhero character The Shield , the first of the super-patriotic heroes with a costume based on a national flag  (  pre-dating Captain America by over a year  )  , The Comet , who was the first superhero to die , and Archie Andrews , who eventually became the main focus of the company 's extensive range of publications .
